tt emigrated from England to Salem, MA, in 1637; John Wolcott (1632–1690) is recorded in Springfield, MA."],"variants":[{"name":"Walcutt","meanings":["English: variant of   Walcott  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":24,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705190,"age":55,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter de Walcott was born about 1235, in England, his father, Jeran Walcott, was 60 and his mother, Anna Mynde, was 56. He had at least 1 son with de Walcott. He died after 1306."},"et":{"about 1235–after 1306":"umbes 1235–pärast 1306","1211–1302":"1211–1302","1235–1306":"1235–1306","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1265–1316":"1265–1316","1176–1267":"1176–1267","1180–1275":"1180–1275","1275":"1275","1176":"1176","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","1180":"1180","1316":"1316","1259":"1259","1302":"1302","af